11.What kind of storage classes in c and give example also?

  *Storage classes determines that visibility, life time, memory location and what is the initial value of that.
  *There are 4 types of storage classes in c:
    1.auto-By default every variable declared as auto,means no need to mention keyword auto.

    2.static-If any variable declared as a static,that considered as static variable.

    3.extern-If any variable declared as a keyword extern ,that considered as extern/global variable.That can be accessed throughout the program and outside of the program also.

    4.register-If any variable declared as a register,that can be considered as register variable.Mainly register variable is used to execution fast programming,like suppose i want to develop application or
                game which performance will be fast so that variable will be declared inside the  register.

  NOTE:So all variables declared inside RAM but register variable declared inside Registers.


