9.What is the command line argument?

 *Command line argument is used when we want to pass argument from outside the program,means when we want to control of our program from outside in such case we use command line argument.

 Eg: main.cpp
 #include <iostream>
 using namespace std;
 int main(int argc,char**argv) {
    cout<<argv[0]<<endl;
    cout<<argv[1]<<endl;
   
    return 0;
 }

g++  main.cpp
./a.out siva
o/p:
./a.out
siva

