10.what is pointer?

 *Pointer is like a variable which is able to store the address of the another variable,means whenever you want to store the value we use the normal variables and if you want to store the address we can use pointer.
 *In case of pointer,we use 2 symbols asterik(*) and ampersand(&). * is meant for value we are dealing with value & means we are dealing with addresses.


