13.What is polymorphism?

 *Polymorphism means having a many forms (for eg: person behave like student in class,in office behave like employee...etc).
 *polymorphism is categorizied into groups:
  1.compile-time Polymorphism
  2.Run-time polymorphism

The best application for compile-time polymorphism is function overloading.
The best application for run-time polymorphism is function overriding.




14.When we go function overloading and when we function overriding?

 *When we want to overload the name  and we want to perform different operations with the name in such case we use function overloading.
 *Whenever iam not satsifying parent class function so then we should write our own function in child class then in such case we use function overriding. 


