15.what is encapsulation?

 *Encapsulation means binding and grouping the data into single unit.
 *so class is the best example for encapsulation it binds datamembers and memberfunctions together.

Real-life example:
*Capsule is wrapping the data into a single unit so to provide a  flexibility and  protection.so like class protecting  its data memnbers and members with access specifier(public,private,protected).



