17.What is difference between structure and union?

 *Structure is used to create different datatypes.But in case of structure whenever we are mentioning any variables so that whole memory is occupied by this structure.
 *Union is used to create different datatypes.But union is used for the memory management purpose.when we create a union it find which variable is having highest size so only that memory will be allocated
 and that is a shareable memory which is shared by the other variables in case of union.


